This Privacy Policy sets out our privacy practices. Please take the time to review this Privacy Policy as it tells you how your personal information will be treated by us.

60&amp;Sensational Limited t/a SoSensational want to offer you the best possible internet experience. Consequently, additional functions, features, products or services may be incorporated into our site from time to time. This, and our commitment to protecting the privacy of your personal information may result in periodic changes to this privacy policy. As a result, please remember to refer to the privacy policy regularly to review any amendments. If we change our privacy policy we will post the changes on this page and may place notices on other pages of our site.

<strong>What information do we collect?</strong>

You can generally visit this site without telling us who you are and we will not collect any personal information about you except when you choose to provide it. However the more information you volunteer the better we can tailor our services to you.

Where you register or subscribe to our newsletters we collect and process personal information about you including your name, email and postal address and other preferred contact details. We may also ask you for other optional information such as what sorts of subjects or services interest you. If you choose to give us this information we will use it to help us provide you with the best possible service personalised to your needs and preferences.

We may automatically collect non-personal information about you such as the type of internet browsers you use or the site from which you linked to our site. You cannot be identified from this information and it is only used to assist us in providing an effective service on our site. We may from time to time supply the owners or operators of third party sites from which it is possible to link to our site with information relating to the number of users linking to our site from their site. You cannot be identified from this information.

<strong>What do we collect and use personal information for?</strong>

<strong>Where you choose to provide personal information it will be used by us in order to:</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Administer your user subscription, should you register with us.</li>
	<li>Deliver our e-newsletters where you have subscribed to receive these from us.</li>
	<li>Customise the service we provide to you.</li>
	<li>Verify your identity (for example in the event you are a competition winner).</li>
	<li>Carry out surveys and market research</li>
	<li>Send you information and offers about products and services</li>
</ul>
<strong>Disclosing your information to others</strong>

Certain 60&amp;Sensational Limited t/a SoSensational services are provided in conjunction with third party service providers such as mail houses and IT services companies in which case we may need to share your personal information with them in order to provide these services.

Your personal information may be disclosed to a third party as part of a reorganisation or a sale of the assets of a 60&amp;Sensational Limited company or having ensured that steps have been taken to ensure that your privacy rights continue to be protected.

Other than the disclosures referred to in this policy, we will not disclose any personal information without your permission unless we are legally entitled or obliged to do so (for example, if required to do so by Court order or for the purposes of prevention of fraud or other crime).

<strong>Information about products and services</strong>

If you register or subscribe to our e-newsletters we may from time to time, send you, with your consent details of or samples of products and services which we think may be of interest to you. If at any time you do not wish to continue to receive these details then send a blank email to nomarketing@sosensational.co.uk.

In addition, from time to time 60&amp;Sensational Limited t/a SoSensational may share the information you supply to us with selected third parties to enable them to send you, with your consent, information, samples, offers and services which may be of interest to you. If at any time you do not wish us to continue to share your information in this way, then send a blank email to nothirdparties@sosensational.co.uk.

<strong>Security</strong>

The Internet is not a secure medium. We will endeavour to take all reasonable steps to keep secure any information which we hold about you. We have implemented technology and processes to help safeguard your privacy from unauthorised access and improper use (including the storage of your information on secure services protected in secure facilities) and will continue to update these measures as new technology becomes available.

<strong>Transferring your personal information outside the European Economic Area</strong>

As part of the services offered to you through our site, the information you provide to us may be transferred to countries outside the European Economic Area ("EEA"). By way of example this may happen if any of our servers are from time to time located in a country outside the EEA or one of our service providers is located in a country outside the EEA. These countries may not have similar data protection laws to the EEA. If we transfer your information outside the EEA in this way we will take steps to ensure that your privacy rights continue to be protected.

<strong>Third party sites</strong>

We cannot be responsible for the privacy policies and other practices of other sites even if you access them using links from our site and we recommend that you check the policy of each site you visit.

In addition, if you linked to our site from a third party site, we cannot be responsible for the privacy policies and practices of the owners and operators of that third party site and recommend that you check the policy of that third party site and contact its owner or operator if you have any concerns or questions.

<strong>Contacting us</strong>
If at any time you would like to contact us with your views about our privacy practices or with any enquiry relating to your personal information, you can do so by sending an email to us at privacy@sosensational.co.uk. You are entitled to ask for a copy of the information we store about you (for which we may charge a small fee, not exceeding the statutory maximum that may be charged).
